result.name: Grill 28

reviews.text: Absolutely fantastic meal. I ate at 6pm on a Sunday. It wasn't crowded and service was excellent. Great atmosphere and beautiful dining area with cushy chairs and wooden tables. The bar looks well stocked though I don't drink.  I had the pork strip. I will get it again. The menu seemed to have a great variety of meals large and small and the prices are very reasonable from burgers on up to the quite more expensive cuts of meat. And there are other 'non-meaty' choices as well.

Ordered set lunch this morning. Environmental is nice, not busy at all. When visiting a grill, check the salt bottle, it doesn’t seems to work and expected no salt for your steak. The salads are good. The main dish are disappointing. The fish filet taste too much soda powder, not recommended. Grill is ok but the sirloin steak itself doesn’t taste much beef. Definitely not US beef. If you are looking for a quiet place to have lunch, not a bad idea. For foods, may be my luck is not good today.
A nice place for lunch, good food with reasonable price
Happy hour drinks are more expensive than normal price drinks which is very cheeky. Shouldn't be penalised for using the establishments offer
Best baby back ribs I've had in a long time
